snippet: FedEx’s second-quarter earnings soared 23 percent, but it missed Wall Street forecasts because of a lower-than-expected benefit from falling fuel prices.
abstract: FedEx reports its second-quarter earnings soared 23 percent, earning $616 million, or $2.14 a share, in its fiscal second quarter, up from $500 million, or $1.57, in 2013's quarter.
lead_paragraph: FedEx’s second-quarter earnings soared 23 percent, but it missed Wall Street forecasts because of a lower-than-expected benefit from falling fuel prices.

headline.main: Earnings at FedEx Fail to Meet Analysts’ Expectations
headline.print_headline: Earnings at Fedex Fail to Meet Analysts’ Expectations
